  "texts": [
    "For example, consider the situation where we want to obtain a Chern wall solution that is polarized to valley K everywhere.",
    "We construct the initial density matrix by specifying the Wannier states that we occupy.",
    "For the set corresponding to valley K and sublattice potential +∆ max, we occupy quasimomenta K corresponding to orbitals whose average x 1 position lies in region L. Moreover, for the set corresponding to valley K and sublattice potential -∆ max, we occupy quasimomenta K corresponding to orbitals whose average x 1 position lies in region R. In a similar vein, we can design an initial state that converges to the valley wall.",
    "Energetic Competition Between Chern and Valley WallsThere will be a loss of (negative) exchange energy at the DWs, since the system is forced to change its local valley polarization or topology 72.",
    "The system can however smoothly interpolate or 'texture' its local wavefunctions between region L and region R, and thereby reduce the amount of exchange energy lost."
